function jc(e) {
    return e ? parseInt(e, 10) : 0
}
function Py(e, t) {
    const r = e / t;
    return isNaN(r) ? 0 : r
}
function qu(e) {
    const t = Py(e.viewport, e.content)
      , r = e.scrollbar.paddingStart + e.scrollbar.paddingEnd
      , n = (e.scrollbar.size - r) * t;
    return Math.max(n, 18)
}
function ZT(e, t, r, n="ltr") {
    const a = qu(r)
      , i = a / 2
      , o = t || i
      , s = a - o
      , l = r.scrollbar.paddingStart + o
      , u = r.scrollbar.size - r.scrollbar.paddingEnd - s
      , f = r.content - r.viewport
      , d = n === "ltr" ? [0, f] : [f * -1, 0];
    return Ny([l, u], d)(e)
}
function Dm(e, t, r="ltr") {
    const n = qu(t)
      , a = t.scrollbar.paddingStart + t.scrollbar.paddingEnd
      , i = t.scrollbar.size - a
      , o = t.content - t.viewport
      , s = i - n
      , l = r === "ltr" ? [0, o] : [o * -1, 0]
      , u = uT(e, l);
    return Ny([0, o], [0, s])(u)
}

function eb(e) {
    this._ += e[0];
    for (let t = 1, r = e.length; t < r; ++t)
        this._ += arguments[t] + e[t]

function XP(e) {
    let t = Math.floor(e);
    if (!(t >= 0))
        throw new Error(`invalid digits: ${e}`);
    if (t > 15)
        return eb;
    const r = 10 ** t;
    return function(n) {
        this._ += n[0];
        for (let a = 1, i = n.length; a < i; ++a)
            this._ += Math.round(arguments[a] * r) / r + n[a]
    }
}
class YP {
    constructor(t) {
        this._x0 = this._y0 = this._x1 = this._y1 = null,
        this._ = "",
        this._append = t == null ? eb : XP(t)
    }
    moveTo(t, r) {
        this._append`M${this._x0 = this._x1 = +t},${this._y0 = this._y1 = +r}`
    }
    closePath() {
        this._x1 !== null && (this._x1 = this._x0,
        this._y1 = this._y0,
        this._append`Z`)
    }
    lineTo(t, r) {
        this._append`L${this._x1 = +t},${this._y1 = +r}`
    }
    quadraticCurveTo(t, r, n, a) {
        this._append`Q${+t},${+r},${this._x1 = +n},${this._y1 = +a}`
    }
    bezierCurveTo(t, r, n, a, i, o) {
        this._append`C${+t},${+r},${+n},${+a},${this._x1 = +i},${this._y1 = +o}`
    }
    arcTo(t, r, n, a, i) {
        if (t = +t,
        r = +r,
        n = +n,
        a = +a,
        i = +i,
        i < 0)
            throw new Error(`negative radius: ${i}`);
        let o = this._x1
          , s = this._y1
          , l = n - t
          , u = a - r
          , f = o - t
          , d = s - r
          , h = f * f + d * d;
        if (this._x1 === null)
            this._append`M${this._x1 = t},${this._y1 = r}`;
        else if (h > fi)
            if (!(Math.abs(d * l - u * f) > fi) || !i)
                this._append`L${this._x1 = t},${this._y1 = r}`;
            else {
                let p = n - o
                  , v = a - s
                  , m = l * l + u * u
                  , g = p * p + v * v
                  , _ = Math.sqrt(m)
                  , y = Math.sqrt(h)
                  , b = i * Math.tan((md - Math.acos((m + h - g) / (2 * _ * y))) / 2)
                  , E = b / y
                  , S = b / _;
                Math.abs(E - 1) > fi && this._append`L${t + E * f},${r + E * d}`,
                this._append`A${i},${i},0,0,${+(d * p > f * v)},${this._x1 = t + S * l},${this._y1 = r + S * u}`
            }
    }
    arc(t, r, n, a, i, o) {
        if (t = +t,
        r = +r,
        n = +n,
        o = !!o,
        n < 0)
            throw new Error(`negative radius: ${n}`);
        let s = n * Math.cos(a)
          , l = n * Math.sin(a)
          , u = t + s
          , f = r + l
          , d = 1 ^ o
          , h = o ? a - i : i - a;
        this._x1 === null ? this._append`M${u},${f}` : (Math.abs(this._x1 - u) > fi || Math.abs(this._y1 - f) > fi) && this._append`L${u},${f}`,
        n && (h < 0 && (h = h % vd + vd),
        h > qP ? this._append`A${n},${n},0,1,${d},${t - s},${r - l}A${n},${n},0,1,${d},${this._x1 = u},${this._y1 = f}` : h > fi && this._append`A${n},${n},0,${+(h >= md)},${d},${this._x1 = t + n * Math.cos(i)},${this._y1 = r + n * Math.sin(i)}`)
    }
    rect(t, r, n, a) {
        this._append`M${this._x0 = this._x1 = +t},${this._y0 = this._y1 = +r}h${n = +n}v${+a}h${-n}Z`
    }
    toString() {
        return this._
    }
}
function Zh(e) {

            t = null;

                throw new RangeError(`invalid digits: ${r}`);

        }

    }
    ,
    () => new YP(t)

class ib {

        this._x = r

        this._line = 0
    }
    areaEnd() {
        this._line = NaN
    }
    lineStart() {
        this._point = 0
    }
    lineEnd() {
        (this._line || this._line !== 0 && this._point === 1) && this._context.closePath(),
        this._line = 1 - this._line
    }
    point(t, r) {
        switch (t = +t,
        r = +r,
        this._point) {
        case 0:
            {
                this._point = 1,
                this._line ? this._context.lineTo(t, r) : this._context.moveTo(t, r);

    }

  , MN = function(t, r, n) {

    case "cross":
        return 5 * t * t / 9;
    case "diamond":
        return .5 * t * t / Math.sqrt(3);
    case "square":
        return t * t;
    case "star":
        {

            return 1.25 * t * t * (Math.tan(a) - Math.tan(a * 2) * Math.pow(Math.tan(a), 2))

}

function Mw(e, t) {

        i = -i,

    Nt ? xt(t, d) : t

function Zn(e, t, r) {
    if (e !== ~~e || e < t || e > r)
        throw Error(_i + e)

function Xn(e) {
    var t, r, n, a = e.length - 1, i = "", o = e[0];
    if (a > 0) {
        for (i += o,
        t = 1; t < a; t++)
            n = e[t] + "",
            r = Et - n.length,
            r && (i += Fa(r)),
            i += n;
        o = e[t],
        n = o + "",
        r = Et - n.length,
        r && (i += Fa(r))
    } else if (o === 0)
        return "0";
    for (; o % 10 === 0; )
        o /= 10;
    return i + o
}
var ma = function() {
    function e(n, a) {
        var i, o = 0, s = n.length;
        for (n = n.slice(); s--; )
            i = n[s] * a + o,
            n[s] = i % tr | 0,
            o = i / tr | 0;
        return o && n.unshift(o),
        n
    }
    function t(n, a, i, o) {
        var s, l;
        if (i != o)
            l = i > o ? 1 : -1;
        else
            for (s = l = 0; s < i; s++)
                if (n[s] != a[s]) {
                    l = n[s] > a[s] ? 1 : -1;
                    break
                }
        return l
    }
    function r(n, a, i) {
        for (var o = 0; i--; )
            n[i] -= o,
            o = n[i] < a[i] ? 1 : 0,
            n[i] = o * tr + n[i] - a[i];
        for (; !n[0] && n.length > 1; )
            n.shift()
    }
    return function(n, a, i, o) {
        var s, l, u, f, d, h, p, v, m, g, _, y, b, E, S, w, T, j, O = n.constructor, B = n.s == a.s ? 1 : -1, I = n.d, R = a.d;
        if (!n.s)
            return new O(n);
        if (!a.s)
            throw Error(gn + "Division by zero");
        for (l = n.e - a.e,
        T = R.length,
        S = I.length,
        p = new O(B),
        v = p.d = [],
        u = 0; R[u] == (I[u] || 0); )
            ++u;
        if (R[u] > (I[u] || 0) && --l,
        i == null ? y = i = O.precision : o ? y = i + (Gt(n) - Gt(a)) + 1 : y = i,
        y < 0)
            return new O(0);
        if (y = y / Et + 2 | 0,
        u = 0,
        T == 1)
            for (f = 0,
            R = R[0],
            y++; (u < S || f) && y--; u++)
                b = f * tr + (I[u] || 0),
                v[u] = b / R | 0,
                f = b % R | 0;
        else {
            for (f = tr / (R[0] + 1) | 0,
            f > 1 && (R = e(R, f),
            I = e(I, f),
            T = R.length,
            S = I.length),
            E = T,
            m = I.slice(0, T),
            g = m.length; g < T; )
                m[g++] = 0;
            j = R.slice(),
            j.unshift(0),
            w = R[0],
            R[1] >= tr / 2 && ++w;
            do
                f = 0,
                s = t(R, m, T, g),
                s < 0 ? (_ = m[0],
                T != g && (_ = _ * tr + (m[1] || 0)),
                f = _ / w | 0,
                f > 1 ? (f >= tr && (f = tr - 1),
                d = e(R, f),
                h = d.length,
                g = m.length,
                s = t(d, m, h, g),
                s == 1 && (f--,
                r(d, T < h ? j : R, h))) : (f == 0 && (s = f = 1),
                d = R.slice()),
                h = d.length,
                h < g && d.unshift(0),
                r(m, d, g),
                s == -1 && (g = m.length,
                s = t(R, m, T, g),
                s < 1 && (f++,
                r(m, T < g ? j : R, g))),
                g = m.length) : s === 0 && (f++,
                m = [0]),
                v[u++] = f,
                s && m[0] ? m[g++] = I[E] || 0 : (m = [I[E]],
                g = 1);
            while ((E++ < S || m[0] !== void 0) && y--)
        }
        return v[0] || v.shift(),
        p.e = l,
        xt(p, o ? i + Gt(p) + 1 : i)
    }
}();
function Fw(e, t) {
    var r, n, a, i, o, s, l = 0, u = 0, f = e.constructor, d = f.precision;
    if (Gt(e) > 16)
        throw Error(Ip + Gt(e));
    if (!e.s)
        return new f(en);
    for (t == null ? (Nt = !1,
    s = d) : s = t,
    o = new f(.03125); e.abs().gte(.1); )
        e = e.times(o),
        u += 5;
    for (n = Math.log(hi(2, u)) / Math.LN10 * 2 + 5 | 0,
    s += n,
    r = a = i = new f(en),
    f.precision = s; ; ) {
        if (a = xt(a.times(e), s),
        r = r.times(++l),
        o = i.plus(ma(a, r, s)),
        Xn(o.d).slice(0, s) === Xn(i.d).slice(0, s)) {
            for (; u--; )
                i = xt(i.times(i), s);
            return f.precision = d,
            t == null ? (Nt = !0,
            xt(i, d)) : i
        }
        i = o
    }
}
function Gt(e) {
    for (var t = e.e * Et, r = e.d[0]; r >= 10; r /= 10)
        t++;
    return t
}
function F0(e, t, r) {
    if (t > e.LN10.sd())
        throw Nt = !0,
        r && (e.precision = r),
        Error(gn + "LN10 precision limit exceeded");

function Fa(e) {
    for (var t = ""; e--; )
        t += "0";
    return t

function Zs(e, t) {
    var r, n, a, i, o, s, l, u, f, d = 1, h = 10, p = e, v = p.d, m = p.constructor, g = m.precision;
    if (p.s < 1)
        throw Error(gn + (p.s ? "NaN" : "-Infinity"));
    if (p.eq(en))
        return new m(0);
    if (t == null ? (Nt = !1,
    u = g) : u = t,
    p.eq(10))
        return t == null && (Nt = !0),
        F0(m, u);
    if (u += h,
    m.precision = u,
    r = Xn(v),
    n = r.charAt(0),
    i = Gt(p),
    Math.abs(i) < 15e14) {
        for (; n < 7 && n != 1 || n == 1 && r.charAt(1) > 3; )
            p = p.times(e),
            r = Xn(p.d),
            n = r.charAt(0),
            d++;

        n > 1 ? (p = new m("0." + r),
        i++) : p = new m(n + "." + r.slice(1))
    } else
        return l = F0(m, u + 2, g).times(i + ""),
        p = Zs(new m(n + "." + r.slice(1)), u - h).plus(l),
        m.precision = g,
        t == null ? (Nt = !0,
        xt(p, g)) : p;
    for (s = o = p = ma(p.minus(en), p.plus(en), u),
    f = xt(p.times(p), u),
    a = 3; ; ) {
        if (o = xt(o.times(f), u),
        l = s.plus(ma(o, new m(a), u)),
        Xn(l.d).slice(0, u) === Xn(s.d).slice(0, u))

            m.precision = g,

            xt(s, g)) : s;
        s = l,
        a += 2
    }
}
function Wg(e, t) {
    var r, n, a;
    for ((r = t.indexOf(".")) > -1 && (t = t.replace(".", "")),
    (n = t.search(/e/i)) > 0 ? (r < 0 && (r = n),
    r += +t.slice(n + 1),
    t = t.substring(0, n)) : r < 0 && (r = t.length),
    n = 0; t.charCodeAt(n) === 48; )
        ++n;
    for (a = t.length; t.charCodeAt(a - 1) === 48; )
        --a;
    if (t = t.slice(n, a),
    t) {
        if (a -= n,
        r = r - n - 1,
        e.e = rs(r / Et),
        e.d = [],
        n = (r + 1) % Et,
        r < 0 && (n += Et),
        n < a) {
            for (n && e.d.push(+t.slice(0, n)),
            a -= Et; n < a; )
                e.d.push(+t.slice(n, n += Et));
            t = t.slice(n),
            n = Et - t.length
        } else
            n -= a;
        for (; n--; )
            t += "0";
        if (e.d.push(+t),
        Nt && (e.e > nu || e.e < -nu))
            throw Error(Ip + r)
    } else
        e.s = 0,
        e.e = 0,
        e.d = [0];
    return e
}
function xt(e, t, r) {
    var n, a, i, o, s, l, u, f, d = e.d;
    for (o = 1,
    i = d[0]; i >= 10; i /= 10)
        o++;
    if (n = t - o,
    n < 0)
        n += Et,
        a = t,
        u = d[f = 0];
    else {
        if (f = Math.ceil((n + 1) / Et),
        i = d.length,
        f >= i)
            return e;
        for (u = i = d[f],
        o = 1; i >= 10; i /= 10)
            o++;
        n %= Et,
        a = n - Et + o
    }
    if (r !== void 0 && (i = hi(10, o - a - 1),
    s = u / i % 10 | 0,
    l = t < 0 || d[f + 1] !== void 0 || u % i,
    l = r < 4 ? (s || l) && (r == 0 || r == (e.s < 0 ? 3 : 2)) : s > 5 || s == 5 && (r == 4 || l || r == 6 && (n > 0 ? a > 0 ? u / hi(10, o - a) : 0 : d[f - 1]) % 10 & 1 || r == (e.s < 0 ? 8 : 7))),
    t < 1 || !d[0])
        return l ? (i = Gt(e),
        d.length = 1,
        t = t - i - 1,
        d[0] = hi(10, (Et - t % Et) % Et),
        e.e = rs(-t / Et) || 0) : (d.length = 1,
        d[0] = e.e = e.s = 0),
        e;
    if (n == 0 ? (d.length = f,
    i = 1,
    f--) : (d.length = f + 1,
    i = hi(10, Et - n),
    d[f] = a > 0 ? (u / hi(10, o - a) % hi(10, a) | 0) * i : 0),
    l)
        for (; ; )
            if (f == 0) {
                (d[0] += i) == tr && (d[0] = 1,
                ++e.e);
                break
            } else {
                if (d[f] += i,
                d[f] != tr)
                    break;
                d[f--] = 0,
                i = 1
            }
    for (n = d.length; d[--n] === 0; )
        d.pop();
    if (Nt && (e.e > nu || e.e < -nu))
        throw Error(Ip + Gt(e));
    return e
}
function Rw(e, t) {
    var r, n, a, i, o, s, l, u, f, d, h = e.constructor, p = h.precision;
    if (!e.s || !t.s)
        return t.s ? t.s = -t.s : t = new h(e),
        Nt ? xt(t, p) : t;
    if (l = e.d,
    d = t.d,
    n = t.e,
    u = e.e,
    l = l.slice(),
    o = u - n,
    o) {
        for (f = o < 0,
        f ? (r = l,
        o = -o,
        s = d.length) : (r = d,
        n = u,

const VG = ["Google Ads", "Facebook", "Instagram", "LinkedIn", "Twitter", "TikTok", "Other"];
function KG() {
    const [e,t] = H.useState(!1)
      , [r,n] = H.useState(!1)
      , [a,i] = H.useState(null)
      , [o,s] = H.useState(null)
      , {toast: l} = py()
      , {data: u, isLoading: f} = kt({
        queryKey: ["/api/admin/campaigns"]
    })
      , d = io({
        resolver: oo(dT),
        defaultValues: {
            name: "",
            platform: "",
            startDate: "",
            endDate: "",
            totalSpend: 0,
            notes: ""
        }
    })
      , h = it({
        mutationFn: async w => await ut("/api/admin/campaigns", "POST", w),
        onSuccess: () => {
            De.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/admin/campaigns"]
            }),
            l({
                title: "Campaign created",
                description: "The campaign has been created successfully"
            }),
            t(!1),
            d.reset()
        }
        ,
        onError: w => {
            l({
                title: "Failed to create campaign",
                description: w.message || "Please try again later",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , p = it({
        mutationFn: async ({id: w, data: T}) => await ut(`/api/admin/campaigns/${w}`, "PATCH", T),
        onSuccess: () => {
            De.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/admin/campaigns"]
            }),
            l({
                title: "Campaign updated",
                description: "The campaign has been updated successfully"
            }),
            t(!1),
            i(null),
            d.reset()
        }
        ,
        onError: w => {
            l({
                title: "Failed to update campaign",
                description: w.message || "Please try again later",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , v = it({
        mutationFn: async w => await ut(`/api/admin/campaigns/${w}`, "DELETE", void 0),
        onSuccess: () => {
            De.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/admin/campaigns"]
            }),
            l({
                title: "Campaign deleted",
                description: "The campaign has been deleted successfully"
            }),
            n(!1),
            s(null)
        }
        ,
        onError: w => {
            l({
                title: "Failed to delete campaign",
                description: w.message || "Please try again later",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , m = () => {
        i(null),
        d.reset({
            name: "",
            platform: "",
            startDate: "",
            endDate: "",
            totalSpend: 0,
            notes: ""
        }),
        t(!0)
    }
      , g = w => {
        i(w),
        d.reset({
            name: w.name,
            platform: w.platform,
            startDate: typeof w.startDate == "string" ? w.startDate : new Date(w.startDate).toISOString(),
            endDate: w.endDate ? typeof w.endDate == "string" ? w.endDate : new Date(w.endDate).toISOString() : "",
            totalSpend: w.totalSpend,
            notes: w.notes ?? ""
        }),
        t(!0)
    }
      , _ = w => {
        s(w),
        n(!0)
    }
      , y = w => {
        a ? p.mutate({
            id: a.id,
            data: w
        }) : h.mutate(w)
    }
      , b = () => {
        o && v.mutate(o.id)
    }
      , E = u ? [...u].sort( (w, T) => new Date(T.startDate).getTime() - new Date(w.startDate).getTime()) : []
      , S = h.isPending || p.isPending;
    return c.jsxs("div", {
        className: "space-y-6",
        children: [c.jsxs("div", {
            className: "flex items-center justify-between",
            children: [c.jsxs("div", {
                children: [c.jsx("h2", {
                    className: "text-2xl font-bold",
                    children: "Ad Campaigns"
                }), c.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-muted-foreground",
                    children: "Manage your advertising campaigns and track spending"
                })]
            }), c.jsxs(Ne, {
                onClick: m,
                "data-testid": "button-create-campaign",
                children: [c.jsx(_c, {
                    className: "mr-2 h-4 w-4"
                }), "Create Campaign"]
            })]
        }), c.jsx("div", {
            className: "rounded-md border",
            children: c.jsxs(Gu, {
                "data-testid": "table-campaigns",
                children: [c.jsx(Vu, {
                    children: c.jsxs(qn, {
                        children: [c.jsx(Mr, {
                            children: "Name"

function ku(e, t, r) {
    for (var n = e < 0 ? -1 : 1, a = e * n, i = 0, o = 1, s = 0, l = 1, u = 0, f = 0, d = Math.floor(a); u < t && (d = Math.floor(a),
    s = d * o + i,
    f = d * u + l,
    !(a - d < 5e-8)); )
        a = 1 / (a - d),
        i = o,
        o = s,
        l = u,
        u = f;
    if (f > t && (u > t ? (f = l,
    s = i) : (f = u,
    s = o)),
    !r)
        return [0, n * s, f];
    var h = Math.floor(n * s / f);
    return [h, n * s - h * f, f]
}
function pc(e, t, r) {
    if (e > 2958465 || e < 0)

      , a = Math.floor(86400 * (e - n))
      , i = 0

        T: a,
        u: 86400 * (e - n) - a,
        y: 0,
        m: 0,
        d: 0,
        H: 0,
        M: 0,
        S: 0,
        q: 0
    };

    t && t.date1904 && (n += 1462),
    s.u > .9999 && (s.u = 0,
    ++a == 86400 && (s.T = a = 0,
    ++n,
    ++s.D)),
    n === 60)
        o = r ? [1317, 10, 29] : [1900, 2, 29],
        i = 3;

        o = r ? [1317, 8, 29] : [1900, 1, 0],
        i = 6;

        n > 60 && --n;

        o = [l.getFullYear(), l.getMonth() + 1, l.getDate()],

        r && (i = cV(l, o))
    }

    s.m = o[1],
    s.d = o[2],
    s.S = a % 60,
    a = Math.floor(a / 60),
    s.M = a % 60,
    a = Math.floor(a / 60),
    s.H = a,
    s.q = i,
    s
}

function h_(e, t) {

function Xp(e) {
    return e.indexOf(".") == -1 ? e : e.replace(/(?:\.0*|(\.\d*[1-9])0+)$/, "$1")

function iV(e) {

function oV(e) {

      , r = Xp(e.toFixed(12));

function sV(e) {

function lV(e) {

    Xp(iV(r.toUpperCase()))
}
function kh(e, t) {
    switch (typeof e) {
    case "string":
        return e;
    case "boolean":
        return e ? "TRUE" : "FALSE";
    case "number":
        return (e | 0) === e ? e.toString(10) : lV(e);
    case "undefined":
        return "";
    case "object":
        if (e == null)
            return "";
        if (e instanceof Date)
            return Ka(14, h_(e, t && t.date1904), t)
    }
    throw new Error("unsupported value in General format: " + e)
}
function cV(e, t) {

function uV(e, t, r, n) {

    case 98:
        s = r.y + 543;
    case 121:

        case 1:
        case 2:

        default:

            u = 4;
            break
        }
        break;

        }

        }

    case 72:

        case 1:
        case 2:
            l = r.H,
            u = t.length;
            break;
        default:
            throw "bad hour format: " + t
        }

    case 77:

        case 1:
        case 2:

            u = t.length;
            break;
        default:
            throw "bad minute format: " + t
        }
        break;
    case 115:
        if (t != "s" && t != "ss" && t != ".0" && t != ".00" && t != ".000")
            throw "bad second format: " + t;
        return r.u === 0 && (t == "s" || t == "ss") ? Dn(r.S, t.length) : (n >= 2 ? o = n === 3 ? 1e3 : 100 : o = n === 1 ? 10 : 1,

        case "[mm]":

        case "[ss]":

        u = 1;
        break
    }
    var f = u > 0 ? Dn(l, u) : "";
    return f
}
function Ba(e) {

function m_(e, t) {

                    F.dense ? (U[ge[0].r] || (U[ge[0].r] = []),
                    U[ge[0].r][ge[0].c] = ge[1]) : U[pt(ge[0])] = ge[1],
                    Z.e.c < ge[0].c && (Z.e.c = ge[0].c),
                    Z.e.r < ge[0].r && (Z.e.r = ge[0].r);
                    break;
                case 27:
                    ge[14e3] && (Ee[ge[14e3][0]] = ge[14e3][1]);
                    break;
                case 1537:
                    Ee[ge[0]] = ge[1],
                    ge[0] == we && (oe = ge[1]);
                    break
                }
            }, F);
        else
            throw new Error("Unrecognized LOTUS BOF " + C[2]);
        if (U["!ref"] = Vt(Z),
        ee[Se || oe] = U,
        se.push(Se || oe),
        !Ee.length)
            return {
                SheetNames: se,
                Sheets: ee
            };
        for (var Oe = {}, ke = [], Me = 0; Me < Ee.length; ++Me)
            ee[se[Me]] ? (ke.push(Ee[Me] || se[Me]),
            Oe[Ee[Me]] = ee[Ee[Me]] || ee[se[Me]]) : (ke.push(Ee[Me]),
            Oe[Ee[Me]] = {
                "!ref": "A1"
            });
        return {
            SheetNames: ke,
            Sheets: Oe
        }
    }
    function n(C, W) {
        var F = W || {};
        if (+F.codepage >= 0 && Sl(+F.codepage),
        F.type == "string")
            throw new Error("Cannot write WK1 to JS string");

          , oe = At(C["!ref"])

                se === oe.s.r && (we[Z] = Er(Z));

                  , Oe = Se ? (C[se] || [])[Z] : C[ze];

                        (Oe.v | 0) == Oe.v && Oe.v >= -32768 && Oe.v <= 32767 ? ve(U, 13, p(se, Z, Oe.v)) : ve(U, 14, m(se, Z, Oe.v));
                    else {
                        var ke = Ta(Oe);
                        ve(U, 15, d(se, Z, ke.slice(0, 239)))
                    }
            }

        U.end()
    }
    function a(C, W) {
        var F = W || {};
        if (+F.codepage >= 0 && Sl(+F.codepage),
        F.type == "string")
            throw new Error("Cannot write WK3 to JS string");

        for (var oe = 0, Se = 0; oe < C.SheetNames.length; ++oe)
            (C.Sheets[C.SheetNames[oe]] || {})["!ref"] && ve(U, 27, fe(C.SheetNames[oe], Se++));
        var we = 0;
        for (oe = 0; oe < C.SheetNames.length; ++oe) {
            var ee = C.Sheets[C.SheetNames[oe]];

                    }

            }

        U.end()
    }
    function i(C) {
        var W = re(2);
        return W.write_shift(2, C),
        W
    }
    function o(C) {
        var W = re(26);
        W.write_shift(2, 4096),
        W.write_shift(2, 4),
        W.write_shift(4, 0);
        for (var F = 0, U = 0, oe = 0, Se = 0; Se < C.SheetNames.length; ++Se) {
            var we = C.SheetNames[Se]
              , ee = C.Sheets[we];
            if (!(!ee || !ee["!ref"])) {
                ++oe;
                var se = rn(ee["!ref"]);
                F < se.e.r && (F = se.e.r),
                U < se.e.c && (U = se.e.c)
            }
        }
        return F > 8191 && (F = 8191),
        W.write_shift(2, F),
        W.write_shift(1, oe),
        W.write_shift(1, U),
        W.write_shift(2, 0),
        W.write_shift(2, 0),
        W.write_shift(1, 1),
        W.write_shift(1, 2),
        W.write_shift(4, 0),
        W.write_shift(4, 0),
        W
    }
    function s(C, W, F) {
        var U = {
            s: {
                c: 0,
                r: 0
            },
            e: {
                c: 0,
                r: 0
            }
        };
        return W == 8 && F.qpro ? (U.s.c = C.read_shift(1),
        C.l++,
        U.s.r = C.read_shift(2),
        U.e.c = C.read_shift(1),
        C.l++,
        U.e.r = C.read_shift(2),

        W == 12 && F.qpro && (C.l += 2),
        U.s.c == 65535 && (U.s.c = U.e.c = U.s.r = U.e.r = 0),
        U)
    }
    function l(C) {

        W.write_shift(2, C.s.r),
        W.write_shift(2, C.e.c),
        W.write_shift(2, C.e.r),
        W
    }
    function u(C, W, F) {
        var U = [{
            c: 0,
            r: 0
        }, {
            t: "n",
            v: 0
        }, 0, 0];
        return F.qpro && F.vers != 20768 ? (U[0].c = C.read_shift(1),
        U[3] = C.read_shift(1),
        U[0].r = C.read_shift(2),
        C.l += 2) : (U[2] = C.read_shift(1),
        U[0].c = C.read_shift(2),
        U[0].r = C.read_shift(2)),
        U
    }
    function f(C, W, F) {

          , oe = u(C, W, F);
        if (oe[1].t = "s",
        F.vers == 20768) {
            C.l++;
            var Se = C.read_shift(1);
            return oe[1].v = C.read_shift(Se, "utf8"),
            oe
        }
        return F.qpro && C.l++,
        oe[1].v = C.read_shift(U - C.l, "cstr"),
        oe
    }
    function d(C, W, F) {
        var U = re(7 + F.length);
        U.write_shift(1, 255),
        U.write_shift(2, W),
        U.write_shift(2, C),
        U.write_shift(1, 39);
        for (var oe = 0; oe < U.length; ++oe) {
            var Se = F.charCodeAt(oe);
            U.write_shift(1, Se >= 128 ? 95 : Se)
        }
        return U.write_shift(1, 0),
        U
    }
    function h(C, W, F) {

    function p(C, W, F) {

    }
    function m(C, W, F) {
        var U = re(13);

        U.write_shift(2, W),
        U.write_shift(2, C),
        U.write_shift(8, F, "f"),

    }
    function g(C, W, F) {
        var U = C.l + W
          , oe = u(C, W, F);
        if (oe[1].v = C.read_shift(8, "f"),
        F.qpro)
            C.l = U;
        else {
            var Se = C.read_shift(2);
            E(C.slice(C.l, C.l + Se), oe),
            C.l += Se
        }
        return oe
    }
    function _(C, W, F) {
        var U = W & 32768;
        return W &= -32769,
        W = (U ? C : 0) + (W >= 8192 ? W - 16384 : W),
        (U ? "" : "$") + (F ? Er(W) : pr(W))
    }
    var y = {
        51: ["FALSE", 0],
        52: ["TRUE", 0],
        70: ["LEN", 1],
        80: ["SUM", 69],
        81: ["AVERAGEA", 69],
        82: ["COUNTA", 69],
        83: ["MINA", 69],
        84: ["MAXA", 69],
        111: ["T", 1]
    }
      , b = ["", "", "", "", "", "", "", "", "", "+", "-", "*", "/", "^", "=", "<>", "<=", ">=", "<", ">", "", "", "", "", "&", "", "", "", "", "", "", ""];
    function E(C, W) {
        Qr(C, 0);
        for (var F = [], U = 0, oe = "", Se = "", we = "", ee = ""; C.l < C.length; ) {
            var se = C[C.l++];
            switch (se) {
            case 0:
                F.push(C.read_shift(8, "f"));
                break;
            case 1:
                Se = _(W[0].c, C.read_shift(2), !0),
                oe = _(W[0].r, C.read_shift(2), !1),
                F.push(Se + oe);
                break;
            case 2:
                {
                    var Ee = _(W[0].c, C.read_shift(2), !0)
                      , Z = _(W[0].r, C.read_shift(2), !1);
                    Se = _(W[0].c, C.read_shift(2), !0),
                    oe = _(W[0].r, C.read_shift(2), !1),
                    F.push(Ee + Z + ":" + Se + oe)
                }
                break;
            case 3:
                if (C.l < C.length) {
                    console.error("WK1 premature formula end");
                    return
                }
                break;
            case 4:
                F.push("(" + F.pop() + ")");
                break;
            case 5:
                F.push(C.read_shift(2));
                break;
            case 6:
                {
                    for (var ze = ""; se = C[C.l++]; )
                        ze += String.fromCharCode(se);
                    F.push('"' + ze.replace(/"/g, '""') + '"')
                }
                break;
            case 8:
                F.push("-" + F.pop());
                break;
            case 23:
                F.push("+" + F.pop());
                break;
            case 22:
                F.push("NOT(" + F.pop() + ")");
                break;
            case 20:
            case 21:
                ee = F.pop(),
                we = F.pop(),
                F.push(["AND", "OR"][se - 20] + "(" + we + "," + ee + ")");
                break;
            default:
                if (se < 32 && b[se])
                    ee = F.pop(),
                    we = F.pop(),
                    F.push(we + b[se] + ee);
                else if (y[se]) {
                    if (U = y[se][1],
                    U == 69 && (U = C[C.l++]),
                    U > F.length) {
                        console.error("WK1 bad formula parse 0x" + se.toString(16) + ":|" + F.join("|") + "|");
                        return
                    }
                    var Oe = F.slice(-U);
                    F.length -= U,
                    F.push(y[se][0] + "(" + Oe.join(",") + ")")
                } else
                    return se <= 7 ? console.error("WK1 invalid opcode " + se.toString(16)) : se <= 24 ? console.error("WK1 unsupported op " + se.toString(16)) : se <= 30 ? console.error("WK1 invalid opcode " + se.toString(16)) : se <= 115 ? console.error("WK1 unsupported function opcode " + se.toString(16)) : console.error("WK1 unrecognized opcode " + se.toString(16))
            }
        }
        F.length == 1 ? W[1].f = "" + F[0] : console.error("WK1 bad formula parse |" + F.join("|") + "|")
    }
    function S(C) {
        var W = [{
            c: 0,
            r: 0
        }, {
            t: "n",
            v: 0

    function T(C, W, F, U) {
        var oe = re(6 + U.length);
        oe.write_shift(2, C),
        oe.write_shift(1, F),
        oe.write_shift(1, W),
        oe.write_shift(1, 39);

        }

    }
    function j(C, W) {
        var F = S(C);
        F[1].v = C.read_shift(2);
        var U = F[1].v >> 1;
        if (F[1].v & 1)
            switch (U & 7) {
            case 0:
                U = (U >> 3) * 5e3;
                break;
            case 1:
                U = (U >> 3) * 500;
                break;
            case 2:
                U = (U >> 3) / 20;
                break;
            case 3:
                U = (U >> 3) / 200;
                break;
            case 4:
                U = (U >> 3) / 2e3;
                break;
            case 5:
                U = (U >> 3) / 2e4;
                break;
            case 6:
                U = (U >> 3) / 16;
                break;
            case 7:
                U = (U >> 3) / 64;
                break
            }
        return F[1].v = U,
        F
    }
    function O(C, W) {
        var F = S(C)
          , U = C.read_shift(4)
          , oe = C.read_shift(4)
          , Se = C.read_shift(2);
        if (Se == 65535)
            return U === 0 && oe === 3221225472 ? (F[1].t = "e",
            F[1].v = 15) : U === 0 && oe === 3489660928 ? (F[1].t = "e",
            F[1].v = 42) : F[1].v = 0,
            F;
        var we = Se & 32768;
        return Se = (Se & 32767) - 16446,
        F[1].v = (1 - we * 2) * (oe * Math.pow(2, Se + 32) + U * Math.pow(2, Se)),
        F
    }
    function B(C, W, F, U) {
        var oe = re(14);
        if (oe.write_shift(2, C),
        oe.write_shift(1, F),
        oe.write_shift(1, W),
        U == 0)
            return oe.write_shift(4, 0),
            oe.write_shift(4, 0),
            oe.write_shift(2, 65535),
            oe;
        var Se = 0
          , we = 0
          , ee = 0
          , se = 0;
        return U < 0 && (Se = 1,
        U = -U),
        we = Math.log2(U) | 0,
        U /= Math.pow(2, we - 31),
        se = U >>> 0,
        se & 2147483648 || (U /= 2,
        ++we,
        se = U >>> 0),
        U -= se,
        se |= 2147483648,
        se >>>= 0,
        U *= Math.pow(2, 32),
        ee = U >>> 0,
        oe.write_shift(4, ee),
        oe.write_shift(4, se),
        we += 16383 + (Se ? 32768 : 0),
        oe.write_shift(2, we),
        oe
    }

function FX(e, t) {

        case 2:
            r[0] = 4;
            break;
        case 4:
            r[0] = 16;
            break;
        case 0:
            r[0] = 1;
            break;
        case 1:
            r[0] = 2;
            break
        }
    switch (r[0]) {
    case 4:
        r[1] = EK(e, 1) ? "TRUE" : "FALSE",
        t != 12 && (e.l += 7);
        break;
    case 37:
    case 16:
        r[1] = Hl[e[e.l]],
        e.l += t == 12 ? 4 : 8;
        break;
    case 0:
        e.l += 8;
        break;

        r[1] = ls(e);
        break;
    case 2:
        r[1] = PK(e, 0, {
            biff: t > 0 && t < 8 ? 2 : t
        });
        break;
    default:
        throw new Error("Bad SerAr: " + r[0])
    }
    return r
}

function mY(e, t, r, n) {
    if (n.biff < 8)
        return ea(e, t);
    for (var a = e.l + t, i = [], o = 0; o !== r.length; ++o)
        switch (r[o][0]) {
        case "PtgArray":
            r[o][1] = $X(e, 0, n),
            i.push(r[o][1]);
            break;
        case "PtgMemArea":
            r[o][2] = RX(e, r[o][1], n),
            i.push(r[o][2]);
            break;
        case "PtgExp":
            n && n.biff == 12 && (r[o][1][1] = e.read_shift(4),
            i.push(r[o][1]));
            break;
        case "PtgList":
        case "PtgElfRadicalS":
        case "PtgElfColS":
        case "PtgElfColSV":
            throw "Unsupported " + r[o][0]
        }
    return t = a - e.l,
    t !== 0 && i.push(ea(e, t)),
    i
}
function vY(e, t, r) {
    for (var n = e.l + t, a, i, o = []; n != e.l; )
        t = n - e.l,
        i = e[e.l],
        a = oy[i] || oy[dY[i]],
        (i === 24 || i === 25) && (a = (i === 24 ? hY : pY)[e[e.l + 1]]),
        !a || !a.f ? ea(e, t) : o.push([a.n, a.f(e, t, r)]);
    return o
}
function gY(e) {
    for (var t = [], r = 0; r < e.length; ++r) {
        for (var n = e[r], a = [], i = 0; i < n.length; ++i) {
            var o = n[i];
            if (o)
                switch (o[0]) {
                case 2:
                    a.push('"' + o[1].replace(/"/g, '""') + '"');
                    break;
                default:
                    a.push(o[1])
                }
            else
                a.push("")
        }
        t.push(a.join(","))
    }
    return t.join(";")
}
var xY = {
    PtgAdd: "+",
    PtgConcat: "&",

    PtgLt: "<",

    PtgSub: "-"

function yY(e, t) {
    if (!e && !(t && t.biff <= 5 && t.biff >= 2))
        throw new Error("empty sheet name");
    return /[^\w\u4E00-\u9FFF\u3040-\u30FF]/.test(e) ? "'" + e + "'" : e
}
function AS(e, t, r) {
    if (!e)
        return "SH33TJSERR0";
    if (r.biff > 8 && (!e.XTI || !e.XTI[t]))
        return e.SheetNames[t];
    if (!e.XTI)
        return "SH33TJSERR6";
    var n = e.XTI[t];
    if (r.biff < 8)
        return t > 1e4 && (t -= 65536),
        t < 0 && (t = -t),
        t == 0 ? "" : e.XTI[t - 1];
    if (!n)
        return "SH33TJSERR1";
    var a = "";
    if (r.biff > 8)
        switch (e[n[0]][0]) {
        case 357:
            return a = n[1] == -1 ? "#REF" : e.SheetNames[n[1]],
            n[1] == n[2] ? a : a + ":" + e.SheetNames[n[2]];
        case 358:
            return r.SID != null ? e.SheetNames[r.SID] : "SH33TJSSAME" + e[n[0]][0];
        case 355:
        default:
            return "SH33TJSSRC" + e[n[0]][0]
        }
    switch (e[n[0]][0][0]) {
    case 1025:
        return a = n[1] == -1 ? "#REF" : e.SheetNames[n[1]] || "SH33TJSERR3",
        n[1] == n[2] ? a : a + ":" + e.SheetNames[n[2]];
    case 14849:
        return e[n[0]].slice(1).map(function(i) {
            return i.Name
        }).join(";;");
    default:
        return e[n[0]][0][3] ? (a = n[1] == -1 ? "#REF" : e[n[0]][0][3][n[1]] || "SH33TJSERR4",
        n[1] == n[2] ? a : a + ":" + e[n[0]][0][3][n[2]]) : "SH33TJSERR2"
    }
}
function sy(e, t, r) {
    var n = AS(e, t, r);
    return n == "#REF" ? n : yY(n, r)
}
function Go(e, t, r, n, a) {
    var i = a && a.biff || 8, o = {
        s: {
            c: 0,
            r: 0
        },
        e: {
            c: 0,
            r: 0
        }
    }, s = [], l, u, f, d = 0, h = 0, p, v = "";
    if (!e[0] || !e[0][0])
        return "";
    for (var m = -1, g = "", _ = 0, y = e[0].length; _ < y; ++_) {
        var b = e[0][_];
        switch (b[0]) {
        case "PtgUminus":
            s.push("-" + s.pop());
            break;
        case "PtgUplus":
            s.push("+" + s.pop());
            break;
        case "PtgPercent":
            s.push(s.pop() + "%");
            break;
        case "PtgAdd":
        case "PtgConcat":
        case "PtgDiv":
        case "PtgEq":
        case "PtgGe":
        case "PtgGt":
        case "PtgLe":
        case "PtgLt":
        case "PtgMul":
        case "PtgNe":
        case "PtgPower":
        case "PtgSub":
            if (l = s.pop(),
            u = s.pop(),
            m >= 0) {
                switch (e[0][m][1][0]) {
                case 0:
                    g = Rt(" ", e[0][m][1][1]);
                    break;
                case 1:
                    g = Rt("\r", e[0][m][1][1]);
                    break;
                default:
                    if (g = "",
                    a.WTF)
                        throw new Error("Unexpected PtgAttrSpaceType " + e[0][m][1][0])
                }
                u = u + g,
                m = -1
            }
            s.push(u + xY[b[0]] + l);
            break;
        case "PtgIsect":
            l = s.pop(),
            u = s.pop(),
            s.push(u + " " + l);
            break;
        case "PtgUnion":
            l = s.pop(),
            u = s.pop(),
            s.push(u + "," + l);
            break;
        case "PtgRange":
            l = s.pop(),
            u = s.pop(),
            s.push(u + ":" + l);
            break;
        case "PtgAttrChoose":
            break;
        case "PtgAttrGoto":
            break;
        case "PtgAttrIf":
            break;
        case "PtgAttrIfError":
            break;
        case "PtgRef":
            f = $s(b[1][1], o, a),
            s.push(Ls(f, i));
            break;
        case "PtgRefN":
            f = r ? $s(b[1][1], r, a) : b[1][1],
            s.push(Ls(f, i));
            break;
        case "PtgRef3d":
            d = b[1][1],
            f = $s(b[1][2], o, a),
            v = sy(n, d, a),
            s.push(v + "!" + Ls(f, i));
            break;
        case "PtgFunc":
        case "PtgFuncVar":
            var E = b[1][0]
              , S = b[1][1];
            E || (E = 0),
            E &= 127;
            var w = E == 0 ? [] : s.slice(-E);
            s.length -= E,
            S === "User" && (S = w.shift()),
            s.push(S + "(" + w.join(",") + ")");
            break;
        case "PtgBool":
            s.push(b[1] ? "TRUE" : "FALSE");
            break;
        case "PtgInt":
            s.push(b[1]);
            break;
        case "PtgNum":
            s.push(String(b[1]));
            break;
        case "PtgStr":
            s.push('"' + b[1].replace(/"/g, '""') + '"');
            break;
        case "PtgErr":
            s.push(b[1]);
            break;
        case "PtgAreaN":
            p = G1(b[1][1], r ? {
                s: r
            } : o, a),
            s.push(K0(p, a));
            break;
        case "PtgArea":
            p = G1(b[1][1], o, a),
            s.push(K0(p, a));
            break;
        case "PtgArea3d":
            d = b[1][1],
            p = b[1][2],
            v = sy(n, d, a),
            s.push(v + "!" + K0(p, a));
            break;
        case "PtgAttrSum":
            s.push("SUM(" + s.pop() + ")");
            break;
        case "PtgAttrBaxcel":
        case "PtgAttrSemi":
            break;
        case "PtgName":
            h = b[1][2];
            var T = (n.names || [])[h - 1] || (n[0] || [])[h]
              , j = T ? T.Name : "SH33TJSNAME" + String(h);
            j && j.slice(0, 6) == "_xlfn." && !a.xlfn && (j = j.slice(6)),
            s.push(j);
            break;
        case "PtgNameX":
            var O = b[1][1];
            h = b[1][2];
            var B;
            if (a.biff <= 5)
                O < 0 && (O = -O),
                n[O] && (B = n[O][h]);
            else {
                var I = "";
                if (((n[O] || [])[0] || [])[0] == 14849 || (((n[O] || [])[0] || [])[0] == 1025 ? n[O][h] && n[O][h].itab > 0 && (I = n.SheetNames[n[O][h].itab - 1] + "!") : I = n.SheetNames[h - 1] + "!"),
                n[O] && n[O][h])
                    I += n[O][h].Name;
                else if (n[0] && n[0][h])
                    I += n[0][h].Name;
                else {
                    var R = (AS(n, O, a) || "").split(";;");
                    R[h - 1] ? I = R[h - 1] : I += "SH33TJSERRX"
                }
                s.push(I);
                break
            }
            B || (B = {
                Name: "SH33TJSERRY"
            }),
            s.push(B.Name);
            break;
        case "PtgParen":
            var G = "("
              , Y = ")";
            if (m >= 0) {
                switch (g = "",
                e[0][m][1][0]) {
                case 2:
                    G = Rt(" ", e[0][m][1][1]) + G;
                    break;
                case 3:
                    G = Rt("\r", e[0][m][1][1]) + G;
                    break;
                case 4:
                    Y = Rt(" ", e[0][m][1][1]) + Y;
                    break;
                case 5:
                    Y = Rt("\r", e[0][m][1][1]) + Y;
                    break;
                default:
                    if (a.WTF)
                        throw new Error("Unexpected PtgAttrSpaceType " + e[0][m][1][0])
                }
                m = -1
            }
            s.push(G + s.pop() + Y);
            break;
        case "PtgRefErr":
            s.push("#REF!");
            break;
        case "PtgRefErr3d":
            s.push("#REF!");
            break;
        case "PtgExp":
            f = {
                c: b[1][1],
                r: b[1][0]
            };
            var V = {
                c: r.c,
                r: r.r
            };
            if (n.sharedf[pt(f)]) {
                var J = n.sharedf[pt(f)];
                s.push(Go(J, o, V, n, a))
            } else {
                var ie = !1;
                for (l = 0; l != n.arrayf.length; ++l)
                    if (u = n.arrayf[l],
                    !(f.c < u[0].s.c || f.c > u[0].e.c) && !(f.r < u[0].s.r || f.r > u[0].e.r)) {
                        s.push(Go(u[1], o, V, n, a)),
                        ie = !0;
                        break
                    }
                ie || s.push(b[1])
            }
            break;
        case "PtgArray":
            s.push("{" + gY(b[1]) + "}");
            break;
        case "PtgMemArea":
            break;
        case "PtgAttrSpace":
        case "PtgAttrSpaceSemi":
            m = _;
            break;
        case "PtgTbl":
            break;
        case "PtgMemErr":
            break;
        case "PtgMissArg":
            s.push("");
            break;
        case "PtgAreaErr":
            s.push("#REF!");
            break;
        case "PtgAreaErr3d":
            s.push("#REF!");
            break;
        case "PtgList":
            s.push("Table" + b[1].idx + "[#" + b[1].rt + "]");
            break;
        case "PtgMemAreaN":
        case "PtgMemNoMemN":
        case "PtgAttrNoop":
        case "PtgSheet":
        case "PtgEndSheet":
            break;
        case "PtgMemFunc":
            break;
        case "PtgMemNoMem":
            break;
        case "PtgElfCol":
        case "PtgElfColS":
        case "PtgElfColSV":
        case "PtgElfColV":
        case "PtgElfLel":
        case "PtgElfRadical":
        case "PtgElfRadicalLel":
        case "PtgElfRadicalS":
        case "PtgElfRw":
        case "PtgElfRwV":
            throw new Error("Unsupported ELFs");
        case "PtgSxName":
            throw new Error("Unrecognized Formula Token: " + String(b));
        default:
            throw new Error("Unrecognized Formula Token: " + String(b))
        }
        var he = ["PtgAttrSpace", "PtgAttrSpaceSemi", "PtgAttrGoto"];
        if (a.biff != 3 && m >= 0 && he.indexOf(e[0][_][0]) == -1) {
            b = e[0][m];
            var fe = !0;
            switch (b[1][0]) {
            case 4:
                fe = !1;
            case 0:
                g = Rt(" ", b[1][1]);
                break;
            case 5:
                fe = !1;
            case 1:
                g = Rt("\r", b[1][1]);
                break;
            default:
                if (g = "",
                a.WTF)
                    throw new Error("Unexpected PtgAttrSpaceType " + b[1][0])
            }
            s.push((fe ? g : "") + s.pop() + (fe ? "" : g)),
            m = -1
        }
    }
    if (s.length > 1 && a.WTF)
        throw new Error("bad formula stack");
    return s[0]
}
function bY(e) {
    if (e == null) {
        var t = re(8);
        return t.write_shift(1, 3),
        t.write_shift(1, 0),
        t.write_shift(2, 0),
        t.write_shift(2, 0),
        t.write_shift(2, 65535),
        t
    } else if (typeof e == "number")
        return Pi(e);
    return Pi(0)
}

        u[f] = e.bf[f];

}

function Q0(e, t) {

      , n = Uu(r)
      , a = 12
      , i = 0;

    e.t) {
    case "n":
        r[1] = 2,
        uZ(r, a, e.v),
        i |= 1,
        a += 16;
        break;
    case "b":
        r[1] = 6,
        n.setFloat64(a, e.v ? 1 : 0, !0),
        i |= 2,
        a += 8;
        break;
    case "s":

            throw new Error("Value ".concat(e.v, " missing from SST!"));
        r[1] = 3,
        n.setUint32(a, t.indexOf(e.v), !0),

        a += 4;
        break;

        throw "unsupported cell type " + e.t

    return n.setUint32(8, i, !0),
    r.slice(0, a)
}

            }, r);

            _ = J0({
                t: "n",
                v: t[m]

            }, r);

                                                onDrop: x => {
                                                    x.preventDefault(),
                                                    x.currentTarget.classList.remove("border-primary", "bg-primary/5");
                                                    const L = Array.from(x.dataTransfer.files).filter(te => te.type.startsWith("image/")).slice(0, 5);
                                                    if (L.length > 0 && F) {
                                                        const te = new FormData;
                                                        L.forEach(ue => te.append("images", ue)),

                                                        hs.mutate({
                                                            courseId: F.id,
                                                            formData: te
                                                        })
                                                    }

                                                            te.append("setAsMain", (!F.imageUrl).toString()),
                                                            hs.mutate({

                                                            }),
                                                            x.target.value = ""

                                                            children: "Negative"
                                                        }), c.jsx(Fe, {
                                                            value: "NO_RESPONSE",
                                                            children: "No Response"
                                                        })]
                                                    })]
                                                }), c.jsx(Ge, {})]
                                            })
                                        }), c.jsx(Ne, {
                                            type: "submit",
                                            disabled: qi.isPending,
                                            className: "w-full",
                                            "data-testid": "button-add-contact-log",
                                            children: qi.isPending ? "Adding..." : "Add Entry"
                                        })]
                                    })
                                })
                            })]
                        }), c.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "border-t pt-4",
                            children: [c.jsx("h4", {
                                className: "text-sm font-medium mb-3",
                                children: "History"
                            }), c.jsx(Os, {
                                className: "h-[300px]",
                                children: qS ? c.jsx("div", {
                                    className: "py-8",
                                    children: c.jsx(ci, {
                                        size: "sm",
                                        text: "Loading contact history..."
                                    })
                                }) : t0 && t0.length > 0 ? c.jsx("div", {
                                    className: "space-y-3",
                                    children: t0.map(x => {
                                        const L = x.type === "EMAIL" ? Ia : x.type === "PHONE" ? Yl : x.type === "IN_PERSON" ? Ql : Xl
                                          , te = x.direction === "OUTBOUND" ? Em : d0
                                          , ue = x.direction === "OUTBOUND" ? "bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-900 dark:text-blue-300 border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800" : "bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 dark:bg-emerald-900 dark:text-emerald-300 border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800"
                                          , qe = x.outcome === "POSITIVE" ? "bg-green-100 text-green-700 dark:bg-green-900 dark:text-green-300" : x.outcome === "NEGATIVE" ? "bg-red-100 text-red-700 dark:bg-red-900 dark:text-red-300" : x.outcome === "NEUTRAL" ? "bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300" : x.outcome === "NO_RESPONSE" ? "bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700 dark:bg-yellow-900 dark:text-yellow-300" : "";
                                        return c.jsxs("div", {
                                            className: `border rounded-md p-3 space-y-2 ${x.direction === "INBOUND" ? "bg-emerald-50/50 dark:bg-emerald-950/20" : ""}`,
                                            "data-testid": `contact-log-${x.id}`,
                                            children: [c.jsxs("div", {
                                                className: "flex items-start justify-between gap-2",
                                                children: [c.jsxs("div", {
                                                    className: "flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap",
                                                    children: [c.jsx(L, {
                                                        className: "h-4 w-4 text-muted-foreground"
                                                    }), c.jsx($e, {
                                                        variant: "outline",
                                                        children: x.type.replace("_", " ")
                                                    }), c.jsxs($e, {
                                                        variant: "outline",
                                                        className: ue,
                                                        children: [c.jsx(te, {
                                                            className: "h-3 w-3 mr-1"
                                                        }), x.direction === "OUTBOUND" ? "Sent" : "Received"]
                                                    }), x.outcome && c.jsx($e, {
                                                        variant: "secondary",
                                                        className: qe,
                                                        children: x.outcome.replace("_", " ")
                                                    })]
                                                }), c.jsx("span", {
                                                    className: "text-xs text-muted-foreground whitespace-nowrap",
                                                    children: Ct(new Date(x.loggedAt), "PP p")
                                                })]
                                            }), x.subject && c.jsx("p", {
                                                className: "font-medium text-sm",
                                                children: x.subject
                                            }), c.jsx("p", {
                                                className: "text-sm text-muted-foreground whitespace-pre-wrap",
                                                children: x.body
                                            })]
                                        }, x.id)
                                    }
                                    )
                                }) : c.jsx("div", {
                                    className: "text-center py-8 text-muted-foreground",
                                    children: "No contact history yet"
                                })
                            })]
                        })]
                    }), c.jsx(la, {
                        children: c.jsx(Ne, {
                            type: "button",
                            variant: "outline",
                            onClick: () => W(null),
                            "data-testid": "button-close-contact-logs",
                            children: "Close"
                        })
                    })]
                })
            })]
        })]
    })
}
export {XZ as default};
